<!--
  This list describes the examples to show in the Examples portal.

  Examples can be grouped. All example elements must have an id. The id must not contain any '/'.
  If a path attribute is present, the path is used to find the directory where the example is
  located. Otherwise, the id is used as a path.

  Each example directory must contain:

  o page-flow.xml: the page flow for the example
  o example-descriptor.xml: a detailed description of the example

  Each example's page flow must support pages with paths starting with the example id. For example,
  if the example id is "xforms-submit", the initial path will be "/xforms-submit", and other page
  paths must start with "/xforms-submit", for example "/xforms-submit/page2". If an example has only
  one page, it can simply use "*" as path for that page. Note that the example id is used, NOT the
  example path.

  Portlets cannot serve resources directly. Examples that want to serve dynamic resources must
  prepend "/example-resources/" to the paths in the page flow. The examples framework will
  automatically dispatch the requests for such resources. For example, the Image Server example
  serves dynamic images with the following:

  <page path-info="/example-resources/imageserver/image" xforms="form.xml" model="image.xpl"/>

  Examples with standalone="true" live in the examples-standalone directory. They do not run as
  portlets.
-->
